       <div class="clear_margin">
       </div>
       <p>
        Nestled in the heart of Edinburgh’s historic city centre our
                Broughton Street shop has been selling a rich variety of
                groceries to the public for over 40 years. Meanwhile on the
                other side of the city and part of the vibrant Tollcross
                community is our second shop which has its own devotees who have
                been buying healthy groceries there for many years. With over a
                thousand customers coming through our doors every day, over the
                years we have provided good quality, natural, wholefood
                groceries to millions of Edinburgh locals and to holiday makers
                and visitors as well.
       </p>
       <p>
        Throughout all our years of selling groceries, we have remained
                deeply committed to our ecological principles, reusing and
                recycling all that we can. Since they first opened their doors
                to the public Real Foods shops have offered dried groceries
                packed from the sack into customer’s own containers and loose
                organic fruit and vegetables that can be carried home in paper
                bags rather than plastic ones. Our own brand groceries, Real
                Foods Essentials and Real Foods Organics have always been packed
                in fully compostable, cellulose bags rather than in plastic, so
                even when you take one of our packets off the shelves you know
                that you are not only benefitting yourself and your own health,
                you are also acting responsibly towards our planet.
       </p>
       <p>
        When you buy your groceries at Real Foods you know that you are
                supporting your family’s wellbeing by feeding them healthy
                wholefoods and by helping to care for the wonderful planet on
                which we all live!
       </p>
